rComments: Professor O'Neill is an average professor. She does well to cover all the material that she includes on the exam, making high grades well within reach. However, she does not typically make her lectures engaging. In addition, she comes off as very callous and unwilling to help on assignments. I don't plan on taking another course with her.

She is a quite nice professor, Going to her office hours is a good way to improve your grades because she is always helpful to answer questions. The lecture slide is a  simple but some readings are hard, but it is okay because she will go through the reading material in the lecture, so please do not skip the class!

Professor ONeil is one of the best professors i've ever had at utsc. The readings are tough to understand however her lectures thoroughly go through the readings. Must go to lectures to understand the concepts and readings, ppt slides have few sentences on them.  Her office hours are the best, she is always willing to help, clarify concepts further
